Among the nine extant families of termites, the family Termitidae Latreille, 1802 is the most speciose and accounts for 71% of the total termites (
Krishna et al. 2013
). They are widely distributed, but are dominant in tropical regions, particularly in the rain forests and savannas ( Eggleton 2011 ). Of the four subfamilies, Macrotermitinae Kemner, 1934, Apicotermitinae Grassé & Noirot, 1955, Nasutitermitinae Hare, 1937 and Termitinae Latreille, 1802 reported from India , Termitinae is the richest in species diversity.

